1
00:00:00,812 --> 00:00:05,392
Want to make your accessibility statement page easier for your customers to find?

2
00:00:05,822 --> 00:00:11,542
In this video, I'll show you exactly how to add a page to your Shopify menu.

3
00:00:11,542 --> 00:00:13,992
So your customers can access it effortlessly.

4
00:00:14,482 --> 00:00:17,822
If you're new to Shopify or just getting started, don't worry.

5
00:00:18,042 --> 00:00:19,952
I'll walk you through each step clearly.

6
00:00:20,382 --> 00:00:25,972
By the end of this video, you'll know how to link any page to your store's navigation.

7
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,992
Making browsing intuitive for everyone.

8
00:00:28,492 --> 00:00:30,682
Step 1: From your Shopify dashboard,

9
00:00:30,682 --> 00:00:33,882
click on content then select menus.

10
00:00:34,202 --> 00:00:35,932
This is where you manage all your stores menus.

11
00:00:36,442 --> 00:00:38,512
Step 2: Choose the menu you want to edit.

12
00:00:38,512 --> 00:00:43,492
For this video, we'll use the footer menu which appears at the bottom of your store.

13
00:00:43,492 --> 00:00:44,792
Click on it to see the existing menu items.

14
00:00:44,792 --> 00:00:45,992
Step 3:

15
00:00:46,262 --> 00:00:47,752
Click on add menu item.

16
00:00:48,012 --> 00:00:50,912
Enter the name of the new item, for example,

17
00:00:51,192 --> 00:00:52,622
accessibility statement.

18
00:00:53,042 --> 00:00:56,382
Step 4: Link this menu item to the page you want it to lead to.

19
00:00:56,792 --> 00:00:59,622
Since this is an accessibility statement,

20
00:00:59,622 --> 00:01:01,892
select your accessibility statement page.

21
00:01:02,112 --> 00:01:03,042
Step 5:

22
00:01:03,452 --> 00:01:04,802
Click save to update the menu.

23
00:01:05,042 --> 00:01:07,432
Step 6: Go to your online store and click up here to view your store.

24
00:01:08,092 --> 00:01:12,652
You'll see the accessibility statement page successfully added to your footer menu.

25
00:01:13,112 --> 00:01:14,792
Ready for your customers to access easily.

26
00:01:15,002 --> 00:01:18,502
Now your Shopify menu is updated and your customers can navigate your store more easily.

27
00:01:19,202 --> 00:01:22,862
Don't forget to try it yourself and make your store even more user-friendly.